1
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,439
Tingting

2
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:47,879
Why are you waiting outside?

3
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:48,719
It's so cold.

4
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,040
So you do know I'm cold.

5
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,120
Why did you miss dinner again?

6
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,359
I tried my best to make it.

7
00:01:53,359 --> 00:01:54,480
Look, I'm sweating all over.

8
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:56,159
The food is all gone.

9
00:01:56,159 --> 00:01:57,359
There's only some noodles left.

10
00:01:57,359 --> 00:01:58,120
There's no sauce either.

11
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:01,120
No way, Mom wouldn't treat me like this.

12
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,519
She knows I use up a lot of energy working on cases.

13
00:02:02,519 --> 00:02:03,040
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

14
00:02:03,319 --> 00:02:05,159
The case, the case—Is the case more important or am I?

15
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:06,439
Of course the case is more important.

16
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:07,560
Let's go.

17
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,199
You—you're important.

18
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:11,240
You're the hardest case to handle. Hurry up!

19
00:02:18,199 --> 00:02:18,840
Auntie

20
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:19,479
Mom

21
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:21,840
Come, come

22
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:22,719
Come

23
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:24,360
Dad, Liu Ziming, Liu Ziming

24
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,199
Hello, Uncle

25
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,240
You must be Xiao Liu, right? Come in, come in

26
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:27,879
Come on in

27
00:02:28,879 --> 00:02:29,560
Change your shoes

28
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:30,680
Um

29
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,360
Sorry about last time

30
00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:34,879
I had something I couldn't get away from, so I was late

31
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:36,879
It's good to be busy when you're young

32
00:02:36,879 --> 00:02:37,919
Being busy leads to success

33
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:39,159
Perfect timing, the food is ready

34
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,120
Sit down and eat together

35
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:41,199
Come, come, come

36
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:42,360
Pass me the noodles

37
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,560
Give it to me, give it to me, pass me the noodles

38
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,520
Go pour some water

39
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,280
Why do you want to run away every time you see your mom?

40
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,199
Where are you running off to?

41
00:02:50,039 --> 00:02:50,759
Come over here

42
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:52,639
Come, come, Ziming, have a seat

43
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,840
Sit here, you sit here

44
00:02:57,919 --> 00:02:58,439
Slow down

45
00:02:58,439 --> 00:02:59,360
Have some water, have some water

46
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,120
It's delicious

47
00:03:01,319 --> 00:03:02,400
Have another bowl

48
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:04,199
Old Fang

49
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:06,360
Here, let me get you another bowl

50
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,639
You've already had two bowls

51
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,800
We have to make sure Xiao Liu eats enough

52
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,840
Can you still eat more?

53
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,080
Yes.

54
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,879
It's really not easy doing your job.

55
00:03:17,039 --> 00:03:19,800
From now on, no matter how late it is, come eat if you're hungry.

56
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,599
Alright.

57
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,439
Here, Xiao Liu.

58
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:23,520
Thank you, Uncle.

59
00:03:23,919 --> 00:03:24,800
Thank you, Auntie.

60
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,319
Why are you still calling us Uncle and Auntie?

61
00:03:27,319 --> 00:03:28,840
Shouldn't you change what you call us now?

62
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,319
So soon?

63
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:33,800
Xiao Liu,

64
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,400
I heard from Tingting,

65
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,439
that you two want to get married.

66
00:03:38,439 --> 00:03:39,080
Yes.

67
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,840
What does your family think?

68
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,800
Have you discussed it?

69
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,439
We have.

70
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:43,400
They have no objections.

71
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,280
It's all settled.

72
00:03:46,159 --> 00:03:49,599
Tingting gets along really well with my sister.

73
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:51,800
His sister is a really good person.

74
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,879
She's also very nice to me.

75
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,199
I heard from Tingting that your mother passed away early.

76
00:03:58,199 --> 00:04:00,360
So after you get married in the future,

77
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,960
how will you two live?

78
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,120
Will you live with your dad?

79
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,199
My mom passed away early.

80
00:04:10,879 --> 00:04:12,400
And my dad doesn't really take care of me.

81
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,840
So I plan to move out and live with Tingting.

82
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,920
Actually, I think

83
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:19,720
look,

84
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,519
you and Tingting are both still young.

85
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:23,680
Shouldn't you communicate more?

86
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,000
And get to know each other better?

87
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,000
You’re young people, after all.

88
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,720
Career should come first, after all.

89
00:04:28,079 --> 00:04:29,839
You think you’re capable,

90
00:04:29,839 --> 00:04:31,319
so you want to show off, right?

91
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:35,319
Being a police officer is actually pretty good.

92
00:04:35,319 --> 00:04:36,560
A government employee.

93
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,240
A stable job with official status.

94
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,399
But for you two,

95
00:04:41,439 --> 00:04:43,600
it would be great if you could get an apartment assigned.

96
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,360
Uncle, Auntie,

97
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:52,240
Our group missed out on the housing allocation.

98
00:04:53,639 --> 00:04:55,720
Right now, I can't afford to buy a house either.

99
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,519
So I can only rent for now.

100
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,519
If you mind,

101
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,560
we can wait a bit longer.

102
00:05:02,639 --> 00:05:03,439
No need to wait.

103
00:05:05,399 --> 00:05:07,399
Don't we have an apartment in Xinyuan?

104
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,759
We can just live there.

105
00:05:12,199 --> 00:05:13,079
Come on, Xiao Liu.

106
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:14,040
Here, add some more sauce.

107
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,519
Eat this bowl of noodles while it's hot.

108
00:05:15,519 --> 00:05:16,160
Alright, alright.

109
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,399
Otherwise, it'll get cold soon.

110
00:05:17,399 --> 00:05:18,120
Okay.

111
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:20,959
Eat up.

112
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,639
Thank you, Auntie.

113
00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:23,519
Thank you, Uncle.

114
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,600
I'll head out now.

115
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,000
I'll walk you out.

116
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,319
Come visit when you have time.

117
00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:28,160
Goodbye, Uncle and Auntie.

118
00:05:32,639 --> 00:05:33,680
Why are you glaring at me?

119
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,800
What do you mean by that?

120
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:36,199
What do you mean, "what do I mean"?

121
00:05:37,759 --> 00:05:39,160
I didn't say anything.

122
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:45,120
Do you really need to worry about this?

123
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,639
Is it even your place to disagree?

124
00:05:48,839 --> 00:05:50,120
This is the first time meeting.

125
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,439
Do you even know him?

126
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:54,000
And you agreed so easily.

127
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,839
He's a detective.

128
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,120
In a couple of years, he could be promoted to chief.

129
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,879
Then your daughter would be the chief's wife. What do you know?

130
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,680
There are plenty of people working as police officers.

131
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,199
How many actually become chief?

132
00:06:04,199 --> 00:06:05,519
The job is definitely busy.

133
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,959
In the future, he won't have time for the family.

134
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,800
Our daughter will be the one to suffer.

135
00:06:09,319 --> 00:06:11,000
Is your dad upset with me?

136
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,519
No.

137
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,160
He's just worried about me.

138
00:06:14,199 --> 00:06:15,879
That's why he said those things.

139
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,319
Your dad's concerns aren't wrong.

140
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,120
It's mainly my fault for being so useless.

141
00:06:21,279 --> 00:06:22,279
That's not true at all.

142
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,959
I'm leaving then.

143
00:06:27,439 --> 00:06:28,519
I'm really leaving.

144
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:30,560
Hurry up and go.

145
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,800
Bye.

146
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,519
Good night.

147
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:33,959
Good night.

148
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:36,519
Hurry upstairs.

149
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,560
You haven't even started working at the city bureau yet,

150
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,560
and you're already talking like an official.

151
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:02,759
Already putting on airs.

152
00:07:02,759 --> 00:07:04,120
Don't try that with me.

153
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,240
Now you're even speaking Mandarin to me.

154
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,399
That's no fun, Captain Huang.

155
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:07,360
Who's no fun? You're the one who's no fun.

156
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,439
Let me tell you,

157
00:07:08,639 --> 00:07:10,360
if you don't give me a name,

158
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,959
I'll stay here with you all day if I have to.

159
00:07:11,959 --> 00:07:14,279
The two of us can chat here for two hours.

160
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,920
How should I put it, Captain Huang...

161
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,319
Like you always say,

162
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:19,240
they were all trained by you.

163
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,160
Who doesn't know that?

164
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,160
That's just how things are.

165
00:07:22,959 --> 00:07:24,160
Ziming, that kid,

166
00:07:24,399 --> 00:07:25,480
he's definitely capable.

167
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:28,040
Very strong, and has a lot of potential.

168
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,279
But right now,

169
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:31,439
he's just inexperienced.

170
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,240
Still a greenhorn, a bit too raw.

171
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:37,439
As for Cao Lei, he's good in every aspect.

172
00:07:39,439 --> 00:07:40,959
That's the honest truth.

173
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:43,000
Of course, he does his own work very well.

174
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,759
But Chengcheng has Down syndrome,

175
00:07:45,759 --> 00:07:47,079
and could have a medical episode at any time.

176
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:48,800
We can't ignore that.

177
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:50,160
Right?

178
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:55,279
That's pretty much what I was thinking too.

179
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,360
So there's no one else.

180
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:03,399
We'll have to let Liu Yang fill in for now.

181
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:09,639
They're all your people, you decide, boss.

182
00:08:16,639 --> 00:08:18,160
It looks like the three of you

183
00:08:18,879 --> 00:08:20,800
have all mastered the Wubi input method.

184
00:08:21,199 --> 00:08:22,519
Come on, let me give you a spot check.

185
00:08:22,639 --> 00:08:23,639
Come in, come in, quickly.

186
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:24,879
Come here and listen confidently.

187
00:08:27,959 --> 00:08:28,600
Master.

188
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:42,600
Master, these are the latest cases.

189
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,960
Please take a look first.

190
00:09:16,399 --> 00:09:17,240
Ziming,

191
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,960
Of all of you, I have the highest hopes for you.

192
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,279
But I'm also most worried about you.

193
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,519
Liu Yang overthinks things.

194
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,360
Cao Lei doesn't think enough.

195
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,279
And you, kid, are always so stubborn.

196
00:09:36,399 --> 00:09:37,279
Remember this.

197
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,559
As criminal police,

198
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,440
cases are our life.

199
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,799
But in life,

200
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,080
there can't be only cases.

201
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,919
Understand?

202
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,000
I understand.

203
00:09:50,759 --> 00:09:52,480
You don't really understand yet.

204
00:09:53,679 --> 00:09:55,919
It's okay, you'll get it with time.

205
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,879
Master,

206
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:01,360
Tingting and I are about to get our marriage certificate.

207
00:10:01,519 --> 00:10:03,279
Yes, I know.

208
00:10:04,759 --> 00:10:06,080
When we have a child,

209
00:10:06,519 --> 00:10:08,279
can we still call you Master?

210
00:10:09,679 --> 00:10:10,480
Don't say that.

211
00:10:10,679 --> 00:10:12,759
Stop always dragging me into your messes.

212
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:15,120
Alright, go on home.

213
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:16,399
Let me walk you inside.

214
00:10:16,399 --> 00:10:17,879
No need, I'm fine.

215
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,320
Hurry and go home.

216
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,720
Take it slow, Master.

217
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,840
So what did Wei say?

218
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:42,159
I don't believe it.

219
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,759
He definitely said you’re not good enough for me.

220
00:10:46,799 --> 00:10:47,600
Tingting.

221
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,159
My dad's here.

222
00:10:49,159 --> 00:10:50,039
Let's talk later.

223
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,639
What's up, Dad? Is something wrong?

224
00:10:51,679 --> 00:10:52,360
It's nothing.

225
00:10:56,639 --> 00:10:57,279
Tingting

226
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:01,600
This

227
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,120
What is it?

228
00:11:03,399 --> 00:11:04,360
Open it and see

229
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:10,679
The apartment we have in Xinyuan

230
00:11:10,679 --> 00:11:12,120
I went over and tidied it up

231
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:14,000
It's a bit small

232
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,600
But it's nice and clean

233
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:17,960
You two can make do, it's enough

234
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:22,120
The furniture, bed, and appliances

235
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,159
are basically all there

236
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,120
Just need to buy a new fridge later

237
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,600
If you two want to

238
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,799
renovate it in the future

239
00:11:28,799 --> 00:11:30,440
then you can discuss it together

240
00:11:31,799 --> 00:11:32,240
Dad

241
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,120
Weren't you not in a hurry for me to get married?

242
00:11:34,919 --> 00:11:36,639
Does it matter if I'm in a hurry?

243
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:38,639
Nothing is more important than my daughter's happiness

244
00:11:40,559 --> 00:11:41,919
Your mom agrees too

245
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:43,320
This apartment

246
00:11:44,679 --> 00:11:45,919
will be your dowry

247
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,039
Dad

248
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,519
Dad, why are you so good to me?

249
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:51,919
You're such a big girl now

250
00:11:54,159 --> 00:11:56,600
But the name on the property deed can't be changed

251
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:58,840
It won't change, it won't change

252
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,039
It'll still be in your name

253
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:01,480
It won't change, it won't change

254
00:12:02,159 --> 00:12:03,120
Thank you, Dad

255
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,720
Marriage is even harder than a case.

256
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,120
Hang in there.

257
00:12:31,679 --> 00:12:32,200
Mom

258
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,399
I've brought her here for you.

259
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,360
Her name is Fang Tingting.

260
00:12:36,679 --> 00:12:38,080
If there's anything you're not satisfied with,

261
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,320
just tell her directly.

262
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Speak nicely.

263
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,200
Isn't she speaking just fine?

264
00:12:44,679 --> 00:12:46,480
Mom, everything's fine.

265
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,600
Don't worry.

266
00:12:47,879 --> 00:12:49,519
The two of them will get their marriage certificate in a couple of days.

267
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,559
Take this.

268
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,559
Sis, what is this?

269
00:13:02,559 --> 00:13:03,559
I can't accept this.

270
00:13:03,559 --> 00:13:04,320
Why can't you accept it?

271
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,720
This is for you to renovate your house.

272
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,159
But renovating a house costs so much, and he's so poor.

273
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:10,720
Really, I don't want it.

274
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:11,759
I really don't want it.

275
00:13:11,759 --> 00:13:13,360
What do you mean you don't want it? Say something.

276
00:13:13,759 --> 00:13:15,559
Just take it. My sister has money, it's fine.

277
00:13:16,279 --> 00:13:17,159
Exactly.

278
00:13:17,759 --> 00:13:19,559
Let me tell you, all the dirty and tiring renovation work—

279
00:13:19,559 --> 00:13:21,559
Let him do all the running around, got it?

280
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,000
Thank you, sis.

281
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,200
